{
  "texts": [
    "Assuming the use case of selftriage, previous studies thus did not yet generate a representative set of vignettes.",
    "Results of SAA audit studies that are based on such stimuli might not be generalizable to laypeople's self-triage with SAA in the real world.",
    "The conceptual challenge of generating a representative set of stimuli was recognized in decision-making research decades ago, particularly in the field of ecological psychology rooted in Egon Brunswik's probabilistic functionalism 23.",
    "In his framework, decision-makers infer unobservable conditions (\"latent variables\" or a triage level) from a set of observable information (\"cues\" or symptoms) based on characteristic correlations between certain cues and the latent variable (see Dhami et al.",
    "21 for an overview)."
  ]
}